<section anchor="security-considerations"><name>9. Security Considerations</name>

<t><list style="symbols">
  <t>MTCP does not include built-in encryption. It is RECOMMENDED to run MTCP
over TLS to protect message confidentiality and integrity.</t>
  <t>Authentication (<spanx style="verb">CMD_LOGIN</spanx>) relies solely on a username with no
password or challenge-response mechanism. Deployments SHOULD add
authentication at the transport layer.</t>
  <t>The server MUST validate <spanx style="verb">payload_size</spanx> before reading payload bytes to
prevent buffer overflows.</t>
  <t>Fixed-length string fields MUST be null-terminated within the buffer;
receivers MUST NOT assume null-termination beyond <spanx style="verb">payload_size</spanx>.</t>
</list></t>

<t><vspace blankLines='999' /></t>
</section>
